 replica of the French frigate L'Hermione set sail for the United States in 1780 carried France's Marquis de Lafayette to help American colonists in their war of independence . 
  Lafayette crossed the Atlantic on the original Hermione in 17 80 to tell his friend George Washington that France was sending a military force to help them . 
  The replica fired cannons as it left the military shipyards of Rochefort in southwest France . 
  French President Francois Hollande visited the ship on Saturday . 
  The ship will head for Yorktown, Virginia and stop in Philadelphia and New York . 
 